---
description: Guidelines for TailwindCSS styling conventions including spacing, opacity, and semantic theme variable usage over hardcoded values
globs: *.tsx, *.css, *.scss
alwaysApply: false
---

Spacing and Layout:
- Use `flex gap-n` over `space-y-n`
- Combine with `flex-col` for vertical spacing

Opacity Syntax:
- Use `bg-white/50` over `bg-white bg-opacity-50`
- Apply shorthand opacity syntax consistently

Theme Variables:
- Use semantic theme variables over hardcoded colors
- Prefer `text-muted-foreground` over `text-gray-500`
- Follow design system color tokens

Hardcoded color exceptions:
- Hardcoded Tailwind colors (e.g. `bg-purple-500`, `bg-emerald-500`) are acceptable when the color carries an external, one-shot meaning that does not belong in the design system. Examples:
  - Mirroring a third-party tracker's status palette (Linear issue state types: triage/backlog/started/completed/canceled)
  - Brand colors of an external service (e.g. a "Connect to GitHub" badge)
  - Data viz where the color encodes a category, not UI semantics
- Anything reusable across the app (success/warning/info/muted/etc.) must go through a theme variable.
- When using a hardcoded one-shot color, keep it scoped to the smallest component that owns the meaning — do not propagate it via shared utilities or props.